net.fathomsoft.fathom.tree

Class ElseStatementNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.fathomsoft.fathom.tree.TreeNode
      • net.fathomsoft.fathom.tree.ElseStatementNode

  • public class ElseStatementNode
extends TreeNode
    TreeNode extension that represents the declaration of an "else statement" node type. See decodeStatement(TreeNode, String, Location) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

      • decodeStatement

        public static ElseStatementNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                                java.lang.String statement,
                                Location location)
        Decode the given statement into a ElseStatementNode instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.

        Example inputs include:
        • else
        • else if (!person.canWalk() && !person.isVegetable())
        • else doSomethingInOneLine()
        • else counter++
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a ElseStatementNode instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a ElseStatementNode.
